{"article_id":"FyMRi13ii8qyNQaH","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The House Judiciary Committee became the scene of a fresh partisan clash Thursday","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"as lawmakers pressed ahead with two articles of impeachment against President Trump ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"with majority Democrats turning back a last-ditch bid by Republicans","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to scrap one of them .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"The committee is poised for an initial vote by day 's end","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"that would send the articles to the full House for a historically weighty floor vote as early as next week .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"But first , lawmakers were finalizing the text of the articles during Thursday 's all-day session ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"which became progressively more heated and personal","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"as the afternoon wore on .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"Rep. Jim Jordan , R-Ohio , began the debate Thursday","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"by proposing an amendment","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"that would strike the first article of impeachment altogether ,","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"claiming","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"the evidence did not support the allegations of abuse of power .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"`` This amendment strikes article one","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"because article one ignores the truth , \"","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"Jordan said .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"He pointed to the White House memorandum","depth":14},{"id":18,"text":"documenting President Trump 's July 25 phone call with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky ,","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"claiming","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"it contained no evidence of a quid pro quo","depth":15},{"id":21,"text":"related to Ukraine investigating Trump 's political opponents .","depth":15},{"id":22,"text":"The call is at the heart of the impeachment probe .","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"`` The day","depth":14},{"id":24,"text":"the transcript came out ,","depth":14},{"id":25,"text":"even Chairman","depth":16},{"id":26,"text":"[ Jerrold ]","depth":16},{"id":27,"text":"Nadler said","depth":15},{"id":28,"text":"there was no quid pro quo in the call transcript , ''","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"Jordan said .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"He went on to note","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"that both Trump and Zelensky have stated","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"there was no quid pro quo","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"discussed or pressure placed on Ukraine ,","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"and that in the end Ukraine never took any action","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"or made any announcement","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"regarding any investigation .","depth":15},{"id":37,"text":"Committee Chairman Rep. Jerrold Nadler , D-N.Y. , rejected arguments","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"that Zelensky 's claim of no pressure supported the president 's case .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"`` Of course he said","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"he was n't pressured , ''","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Nadler said .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"`` He has a gun to his head . ''","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Nadler 's statement came","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"immediately before the Democratic majority then shot down Jordan 's amendment by a party-line vote of 23-17 .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Rep. Jim Sensenbrenner , R-Wis. , supported Jordan 's amendment ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"arguing ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"`` There was no impeachable offense here . ''","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"But Democrats argue","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"that witness testimony shows","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"the administration was linking U.S. aid to the sought-after investigations in other ways .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Democratic Rep. Eric Swalwell further claimed","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"that impeachment articles do not have to include statutory crimes","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"because they are not prosecutors --","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"but that Trump ' s actions would satisfy criminal statutes such as bribery .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"This led Rep. Louie Gohmert , R-Texas , to retort ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"\" Well then why aren ' t they in this impeachment document ? ! \"","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"The debate took a personal turn","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"after Rep. Matt Gaetz , R-Fla. , described allegations of drug use and possession by Hunter Biden ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"wondering","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"why Ukrainian energy company Burisma Holdings would have someone like him as a board member .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"Joe Biden 's role in the termination of a Ukrainian prosecutor","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"who was investigating Burisma","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"is at the heart of what Trump wanted Ukraine to investigate .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"Gaetz proposed an amendment","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"to add references to Burisma and Hunter Biden to an impeachment article .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"After Gaetz made his detailed statement about Hunter Biden ,","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Rep. Hank Johnson , D-Ga. , chided him for `` character assassination , ''","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"while saying ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"`` the pot","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"calling the kettle black is not something","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"that we should do , ''","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"drawing laughter from the room","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"for what appeared to be a subtle reference to Gaetz 's 2008 DUI arrest","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"( the case ended up being dismissed ) .","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"Johnson then said","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"that he is not aware of any members of Congress ' history of substance abuse or being arrested for DUI ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"but","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"if he did ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"`` I would n't raise it against anyone on this committee ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"I do n't think","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"it 's proper . ''","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"The final markup process ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"which began Wednesday evening ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"kicked off Thursday with a separate clash between Nadler and ranking member Rep. Doug Collins , R-Ga.","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"Collins argued","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"that Nadler violated House rules","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"by refusing to let Republicans hold a minority hearing prior to the markup .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"`` The chairman was furnished with a demand","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"signed by all Republican members of the committee during the impeachment hearing","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"held on December the Fourth , ''","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"Collins said .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"`` The chairman has refused to respond to multiple additional requests","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"that that hearing be scheduled ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"and at one point actually telling me ...","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"that we 'll rule on it today .","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"Well , we 're here today . ''","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"Nadler claimed","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"that the rules do not require him to grant a minority hearing","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"before taking action .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"Ultimately , the Democrat-controlled committee voted in Nadler 's favor .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"`` This committee has now sounded the death of minority rights , \"","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"Collins bellowed .","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"`` This committee has now become a rubber stamp . ... They do n't care ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"facts be damned . ''","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Rep. Ted Deutch , D-Fla. , countered","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"that there \" is no right \"","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"for the Republican minority to have a separate day of hearings ,","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"and that they did have the opportunity","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"to call witnesses during the previous hearings","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"-- which mainly featured Democrat-sought witnesses .","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"Rep. Debbie Lesko , R-Ariz. , blasted Nadler","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"for claiming","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"that it was unnecessary for the minority to hold a hearing before Thursday 's vote ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"stating","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"it would no longer matter afterward .","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"`` It just continues to amaze me how corrupt , how unfair this process has been from the start , ''","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"Lesko noted","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"that 17 Democratic members of the committee had voted in favor of an impeachment resolution","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"introduced by Rep. Al Green , D-Texas , on separate grounds on July 17 .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"`` That was even before the July 25 call ! ''","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"Lesko said ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"arguing","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"`` you guys have been wanting to impeach this president","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"since he was elected . ''","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"During Wednesday 's evening session , Nadler insisted","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"that it was necessary to impeach the president swiftly , prior to November 's election .","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"`` We can not rely on an election","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"to solve our problems","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"when the president threatens the very integrity of that election , ''","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"Nadler claimed during Wednesday 's session .","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"Democrats from districts","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"that supported Trump in 2016 ,","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"however ,","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"have been less enthusiastic .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"Recent polls have shown declining support for impeachment in key swing states ,","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"with two polls","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"released Wednesday","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"indicating","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"that most Americans did not want Trump removed .","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"Politico reported earlier this week","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"that the numbers were making a `` small group '' of moderate Democrats ,","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"who have held seats in districts","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"where Trump won in 2016 ,","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"nervous about how to vote .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"They instead have suggested","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"Trump be censured ,","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"which would prevent the GOP from holding a potentially damaging Senate trial","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"and give them political cover in the upcoming election .","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"The House is now composed of 431 current members ,","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"meaning Democrats would need 217 yeas","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"to impeach Trump .","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"There are currently 233 Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"so Democrats could lose only 16 of their own","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"and still impeach the president .","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"Among the House Democrats , 31 represent more moderate districts","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"that Trump carried in 2016 .","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"Freshman Rep. Elissa Slotkin , D-Mich.","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"-","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"who flipped a GOP district in 2018","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"that Trump won by seven points in 2016 -","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"told Fox News last month","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"that she was tentatively weighing all the evidence .","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"On Wednesday , she confirmed","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"that she 's still undecided .","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"`` The phones are ringing off the hook , ''","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"she told CNN .","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"`` We literally ca n't pick up the phones fast enough","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"-- and it 's people on both sides of it . ''","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"Republicans , meanwhile , have vociferously opposed the impeachment effort .","depth":6},{"id":171,"text":"The committee 's ranking member , Collins , stated","depth":9},{"id":172,"text":"that Democrats have been trying to impeach Trump","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"since he took office .","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"He echoed the White House 's argument","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"that the impeachment was politically motivated theater , long in the works","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"and foreshadowed openly by Democrats for months , if not years .","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"He and Sensenbrenner each argued","depth":8},{"id":178,"text":"that unlike previous presidents","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"who have faced impeachment ,","depth":10},{"id":180,"text":"Trump was not accused of an offense","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"actually defined by law :","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"neither `` abuse of power '' nor `` obstruction of Congress '' is a recognized federal or state crime .","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"Those are the two offenses","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"outlined in the articles of impeachment before the committee .","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"( The separate charge of contempt of Congress ,","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"according to the DOJ 's Office of Legal Counsel ,","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"exempts the president for separation-of-powers reasons . )","depth":12},{"id":188,"text":"The markup is expected to go until Thursday afternoon .","depth":3},{"id":189,"text":"If the committee votes to approve the articles of impeachment ,","depth":5},{"id":190,"text":"as expected ,","depth":5},{"id":191,"text":"there will likely be an impeachment vote on the House floor in the middle of next week .","depth":4},{"id":192,"text":"The articles center on Trump 's efforts","depth":4},{"id":193,"text":"to pressure Ukraine to launch an investigation into his political rivals","depth":5},{"id":194,"text":"- namely , former vice president Joe Biden -","depth":5},{"id":195,"text":"while withholding aid .","depth":3},{"id":196,"text":"Democrats argue","depth":4},{"id":197,"text":"Trump wrongly used U.S. aid and the prospect of a White House meeting as leverage ,","depth":4},{"id":198,"text":"but Trump denies doing so .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":397,"left":390,"right":396,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":390,"left":386,"right":389,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":386,"left":280,"right":385,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":207,"right":279,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":202,"right":206,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":0,"right":201,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":1,"right":200,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":203,"right":205,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":203,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":205,"left":6,"right":204,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":279,"left":254,"right":278,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":254,"left":242,"right":253,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":234,"right":241,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":234,"left":211,"right":233,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"p